              "description": "Fights on the front lines, taunting enemies to keep them away from allies."
            },
            "introduction": {
              "introduction": "　A defender who can launch all-around attacks while moving.\n\n　Strongholds are subjugation units deployed to prevent further damage in urban warfare. Their heavy reinforced suits prevent nearly all conventional personal weapons.\n　They are mostly composed of retired police officers. As the veterans who remained in battlefields from the Administration Failure to the Grand Purification War, they will gladly draw the attention of enemies with a pistol. They prefer to take on enemy attacks themselves rather than to lose a comrade. "
